        <list id="id74922" display="block" list-type="enumerated"><item id="uid66">For each of the following rotations about the origin:
(i) Write down the rule.
(ii) Draw a diagram showing the direction of rotation.
<list id="id74950" display="block" list-type="enumerated" number-style="lower-alpha"><item id="uid67">OA is rotated to OA<m:math overflow="scroll"><m:msup><m:mrow/><m:mo>'</m:mo></m:msup></m:math> with A(4;2) and A<m:math overflow="scroll"><m:msup><m:mrow/><m:mo>'</m:mo></m:msup></m:math>(-2;4)
</item><item id="uid68">OB is rotated to OB<m:math overflow="scroll"><m:msup><m:mrow/><m:mo>'</m:mo></m:msup></m:math> with B(-2;5) and B<m:math overflow="scroll"><m:msup><m:mrow/><m:mo>'</m:mo></m:msup></m:math>(5;2)
</item><item id="uid69">OC is rotated to OC<m:math overflow="scroll"><m:msup><m:mrow/><m:mo>'</m:mo></m:msup></m:math> with C(-1;-4) and C<m:math overflow="scroll"><m:msup><m:mrow/><m:mo>'</m:mo></m:msup></m:math>(1;4)
</item></list></item>
          <item id="uid70">Copy <m:math overflow="scroll"><m:mi>Δ</m:mi></m:math>XYZ onto squared paper. The co-ordinates are given on the picture.
