</item><item id="uid72">Rotate <m:math overflow="scroll"><m:mi>Δ</m:mi></m:math>XYZ through 180<m:math overflow="scroll"><m:msup><m:mrow/><m:mo>∘</m:mo></m:msup></m:math> about the origin to give <m:math overflow="scroll"><m:mi>Δ</m:mi></m:math>X<m:math overflow="scroll"><m:msup><m:mrow/><m:mo>'</m:mo></m:msup></m:math><m:math overflow="scroll"><m:msup><m:mrow/><m:mo>'</m:mo></m:msup></m:math>Y<m:math overflow="scroll"><m:msup><m:mrow/><m:mo>'</m:mo></m:msup></m:math><m:math overflow="scroll"><m:msup><m:mrow/><m:mo>'</m:mo></m:msup></m:math>Z<m:math overflow="scroll"><m:msup><m:mrow/><m:mo>'</m:mo></m:msup></m:math><m:math overflow="scroll"><m:msup><m:mrow/><m:mo>'</m:mo></m:msup></m:math>. Give the co-ordinates of X<m:math overflow="scroll"><m:msup><m:mrow/><m:mo>'</m:mo></m:msup></m:math><m:math overflow="scroll"><m:msup><m:mrow/><m:mo>'</m:mo></m:msup></m:math>, Y<m:math overflow="scroll"><m:msup><m:mrow/><m:mo>'</m:mo></m:msup></m:math><m:math overflow="scroll"><m:msup><m:mrow/><m:mo>'</m:mo></m:msup></m:math> and Z<m:math overflow="scroll"><m:msup><m:mrow/><m:mo>'</m:mo></m:msup></m:math><m:math overflow="scroll"><m:msup><m:mrow/><m:mo>'</m:mo></m:msup></m:math>.
</item></list><figure id="id75418"><media id="id75418_media" alt=""><image mime-type="image/png" src="../../media/MG11C16_032.png" id="id75418_onlineimage" width="195"><!-- NOTE: attribute width changes image size online (pixels). original width is 195. --></image><image mime-type="application/postscript" for="pdf" src="../../media/MG11C16_032.eps" id="id75418_printimage"/></media></figure></item>
